('chunk_9f88f3325a61aeb1f8','file_a8bb6ddf9d5c59f486','biology.md','Subject-Wide: Common Misconceptions Master List','1. **"Carbohydrates are inherently fattening/unhealthy."** They are the body''s main clean energy source; type and quantity matter, not the category.
2. **"All sugars/fats/proteins are interchangeable."** Simple vs. complex carbs, saturated vs. unsaturated fats, and different amino acid sequences behave very differently.
3. **"Eating enough calories means you can''t be malnourished."** Micronutrient deficiencies ("hidden hunger") occur even with adequate calories.
4. **"Sugar directly rots teeth."** Bacteria produce acid from sugar; the acid causes decay. Enamel cannot regrow.
5. **"Egestion = excretion."** Egestion removes undigested food; excretion removes metabolic waste from cells.
6. **"A denatured enzyme recovers when cooled."** Denaturation permanently destroys the active site.
7. **"Plants get their mass/food from the soil."** Most mass comes from CO₂ fixed in photosynthesis; soil supplies water and minerals.
8. **"Leaves absorb green light."** They reflect green and absorb red/blue.
9. **"Plants store energy as glucose."** They store it as insoluble starch.
10. **"More light always increases photosynthesis."** Only until another factor becomes limiting.
11. **"In osmosis the solute moves."** Water moves across the membrane; solute usually cannot.
12. **"Plants pump water up using energy."** Water rises passively by transpiration pull and cohesion.
13. **"Breathing and respiration are the same."** Breathing moves air; respiration releases energy in cells.
14. **"Lungs convert CO₂ into O₂ / actively suck air."** Gases move by diffusion; breathing is driven by the diaphragm and rib muscles.
15. **"You breathe fast after exercise only for oxygen."** Also to remove CO₂ and repay the oxygen debt (clear lactic acid).
16. **"Muscles push and pull."** Muscles only pull (contract), so they work in antagonistic pairs.
17. **"All joints move."** Fixed joints (e.g. skull) do not.
18. **"Only the smoker is harmed by smoking."** Second-hand smoke harms others too.

---','{"subject":1,"wide":1,"common":1,"misconceptions":1,"master":1,"list":1,"carbohydrates":1,"are":4,"inherently":1,"fattening":1,"unhealthy":1,"they":4,"the":11,"body":1,"main":1,"clean":1,"energy":4,"source":1,"type":1,"and":9,"quantity":1,"matter":1,"not":2,"category":1,"all":2,"sugars":1,"fats":2,"proteins":1,"interchangeable":1,"simple":1,"complex":1,"carbs":1,"saturated":1,"unsaturated":1,"different":1,"amino":1,"acid":4,"sequences":1,"behave":1,"very":1,"differently":1,"eating":1,"enough":1,"calories":2,"means":1,"you":2,"can":1,"malnourished":1,"micronutrient":1,"deficiencies":1,"hidden":1,"hunger":1,"occur":1,"even":1,"with":1,"adequate":1,"sugar":2,"directly":1,"rots":1,"teeth":1,"bacteria":1,"produce":1,"from":4,"causes":1,"decay":1,"enamel":1,"cannot":2,"regrow":1,"egestion":2,"excretion":2,"removes":2,"undigested":1,"food":2,"metabolic":1,"waste":1,"cells":2,"denatured":1,"enzyme":1,"recovers":1,"when":1,"cooled":1,"denaturation":1,"permanently":1,"destroys":1,"active":1,"site":1,"plants":3,"get":1,"their":1,"mass":2,"soil":2,"most":1,"comes":1,"fixed":2,"photosynthesis":2,"supplies":1,"water":4,"minerals":1,"leaves":1,"absorb":2,"green":2,"light":2,"reflect":1,"red":1,"blue":1,"store":2,"glucose":1,"insoluble":1,"starch":1,"more":1,"always":1,"increases":1,"only":4,"until":1,"another":1,"factor":1,"becomes":1,"limiting":1,"osmosis":1,"solute":2,"moves":3,"across":1,"membrane":1,"usually":1,"pump":1,"using":1,"rises":1,"passively":1,"transpiration":1,"pull":3,"cohesion":1,"breathing":3,"respiration":2,"same":1,"air":2,"releases":1,"lungs":1,"convert":1,"into":1,"actively":1,"suck":1,"gases":1,"move":2,"diffusion":1,"driven":1,"diaphragm":1,"rib":1,"muscles":3,"breathe":1,"fast":1,"after":1,"exercise":1,"for":1,"oxygen":2,"also":1,"remove":1,"repay":1,"debt":1,"clear":1,"lactic":1,"push":1,"contract":1,"work":1,"antagonistic":1,"pairs":1,"joints":2,"skull":1,"smoker":1,"harmed":1,"smoking":1,"second":1,"hand":1,"smoke":1,"harms":1,"others":1,"too":1}'